  "prompt": "When is 70% isopropyl rubbing alcohol better than 91%?",
  "response": "70% isopropyl alcohol is generally better than 91% for disinfecting surfaces because:\n\n1. Lower concentration allows more water content, which helps:\n- Penetrate bacterial cell walls more effectively\n- Denature proteins more thoroughly\n- Stay wet on surfaces longer, ensuring proper contact time for killing germs\n\n2. Best uses for 70%:\n- Cleaning and disinfecting hard surfaces\n- Medical/healthcare settings\n- Household sanitization\n- Killing most bacteria and some viruses\n\n3. 91% is better for:\n- Electronics cleaning\n- Quick-drying applications\n- Removing adhesives\n- Where rapid evaporation is needed\n\nIn most disinfection scenarios, 70% is actually more effective at killing microorganisms compared to the higher concentration.",
